@page
@model FlowState.Pages.ResultsModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Results";
}

<section class="fse-page-hero">
    <div class="fse-container">
        <span class="fse-badge">Track Record</span>
        <h1>What FSE Has Built</h1>
        <p>Methodology is only as real as the systems it ships. No proprietary details &mdash; just the shape of the evidence.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="fse-section">
    <div class="fse-container">
        <div class="fse-stats">
            <div class="fse-stat">
                <span class="fse-stat-value">8</span>
                <span class="fse-stat-label">Production Solutions</span>
            </div>
            <div class="fse-stat">
                <span class="fse-stat-value">6</span>
                <span class="fse-stat-label">Industries Covered</span>
            </div>
            <div class="fse-stat">
                <span class="fse-stat-value">12</span>
                <span class="fse-stat-label">Universal Standing Orders</span>
            </div>
            <div class="fse-stat">
                <span class="fse-stat-value">0/0</span>
                <span class="fse-stat-label">Errors / Warnings Target</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="fse-section">
    <div class="fse-container">
        <div class="fse-section-header">
            <span class="fse-eyebrow">Domains</span>
            <h2>Where FSE Has Shipped</h2>
            <p>Six industries, one methodology. The domain changes; the standing orders do not.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fse-card-grid">
            <article class="fse-card">
                <div class="fse-card-icon">H</div>
                <h3>Healthcare Compliance</h3>
                <p>Regulated workflows with hard audit requirements. Living documentation maps cleanly onto compliance evidence &mdash; the state file is the paper trail.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="fse-card">
                <div class="fse-card-icon">L</div>
                <h3>Legal Practice Management</h3>
                <p>Matter tracking, document handling, deadline engines. Predictable behavior beats flashy features when a missed date has consequences.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="fse-card">
                <div class="fse-card-icon">F</div>
                <h3>Financial Trading</h3>
                <p>Systems where correctness is not a preference. Zero-warning builds and the self-healing loop catch what production cannot afford to catch.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="fse-card">
                <div class="fse-card-icon">E</div>
                <h3>Elder Care</h3>
                <p>Operations for caregivers and families. Interfaces that cannot afford to confuse the user &mdash; constraints on the code translate into constraints on the UI.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="fse-card">
                <div class="fse-card-icon">U</div>
                <h3>Education</h3>
                <p>Learning platforms and coursework tooling. New instructors, new learners, new edge cases every term &mdash; the state file absorbs the churn.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="fse-card">
                <div class="fse-card-icon">C</div>
                <h3>Corporate Operations</h3>
                <p>Internal platforms that replace spreadsheets and email threads. The same FSE template onboards them in one session.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="fse-section fse-section-dark">
    <div class="fse-container-narrow">
        <div class="fse-section-header">
            <span class="fse-eyebrow">Invariants</span>
            <h2>What Is True Across Every Solution</h2>
        </div>

        <ol class="fse-timeline">
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">01</span>
                <h4>Consistent Modular Monolith</h4>
                <p>Every solution ships with the same architectural shape. When you know one, you know all of them &mdash; context transfer across systems is free.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">02</span>
                <h4>0-Error, 0-Warning Builds</h4>
                <p>Maintained continuously, not patched before a release. Warnings are errors that haven't escalated yet; we don't let them.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">03</span>
                <h4>One-Session Onboarding</h4>
                <p>A new solution is initialized, described, and brought to green-build state within a single CLI session. The template carries the weight.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">04</span>
                <h4>12 Universal Standing Orders</h4>
                <p>Enforced in every repo, in every session, without exception. Complete files only. No stubs. Zero warnings. CSS tokens only. Secrets never commit. The list is short on purpose.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">05</span>
                <h4>Self-Healing Build Loop</h4>
                <p>Errors are caught by the agent, not by the human, and never by production. Three strikes triggers Counter-Point &mdash; the approach changes, the loop does not spin.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="fse-timeline-item">
                <span class="fse-timeline-step">06</span>
                <h4>Living Documentation Eliminates Context Loss</h4>
                <p>A session that ends at midnight and a session that starts next Tuesday read the same <code>FSE_STATE.md</code>. The human does not re-explain the system.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="fse-section">
    <div class="fse-container-narrow">
        <blockquote class="fse-quote">
            The bar is not "shippable." The bar is "every session ends greener than it started."
        </blockquote>
        <p class="fse-cta-center">
            <a class="fse-btn fse-btn-primary" asp-page="/About">About the Methodology &rarr;</a>
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
